Today, we give you an exclusive look inside a COVID-19 ward, in a hospital in Gauteng, the epicentre of the virus in South Africa. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - As the number of COVID-19 cases continues to rise, eNCA brings you an exclusive look inside a COVID-19 ward in a hospital in Gauteng. COVID-19: SAMA warns of bleak state of health facilities Reporter, Pule Letshwiti joined healthcare workers at the Steve Biko Academic hospital to get a glimpse of their experiences as they wage war against the invisible enemy. Staff says they hope to see some relief from the government's decision to reimpose the ban on alcohol sales. Watch the video above for more details. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.